args: With the dragonblood in hand, Delphi has\nall he needs to complete the forbidden\nritual and bury his tribe's power for good.
He makes his way to one of the Binding Ruins,\nwhere he plans to offer up his soul.
(After this, all will truly be over.\nThe Shards and seals? Lost.\nThe tribe's mission? Forgotten.)
(Now to banish this accursed power\nto the oblivion in which it belongs.)
(All will be well now.\nHe will be...happy.)
I wish I could have seen your smile\none last time...
*pant* *pant* Did I make it?\nAre you still not dead?
Shion?! What are you doing here?
I knew I wanted to see you again,\nbut I'd not thought the feeling so\nstrong as to bring on hallucination.
I'm not an illusion, you idiot!
Now stop this ritual right now!\nIf you don't, you'll die!
N-no! Unhand me! I'm almost there!
Your happiness has never been closer!\nDo not prevent it from happening now!
Did you ever stop to think about MY\nfeelings about this plan of yours,\nyou big idiot?!
You think this will make me happy?!\nHow can I be happy if you're DEAD?!
I NEED you, Delphi! You raised me!\nYou're the only family I have left!
And yet, the Tutelary power. So long as it\nand I exist, your suffering will continue.
And the cruel words I spoke to you?\nAll said with malice aforethought.
Would you claim to need me after all that?
I KNEW something was fishy when you\nstarted saying all those terrible things.
You did it because of me, didn't you?\nTo make me leave so you could go through\nwith this bonkers plan of yours.
I'm not a kid, and I'm not a fool!\nYour plan was thinner than old sheets!
If you really hated me that much,\nyou'd just poison my food or something.
I always ate whatever you made\nwithout question, you know.
Dying is a REALLY crappy way to atone,\nBrother. You can't make up for anything\nwhen you're six feet underground.
Now stop this stupid ritual thing and let's\nfigure out some other way to get you free\nof this power!
I'll help you this time, and we'll\nfind a solution together.
You may think you're a burden to me,\nbut you're actually anything but.
My actions. My schemes. I thought to\nmake you happy, but all I did was\nencumber you with more pain.
I'm sorry, Shion. I'll stop the ritual.
Also, I must make amends with another.
Your Highness? I betrayed your trust.\nStole your very blood. There are not\nwords enough to express my regret.
I will accept whatever punishment you\ndeem appropriate. Merely name it.
I had a feeling it would come to this.\n...Well, maybe not EXACTLY this,\nbut something rather like it.
And seeing as how you still draw breath,\nI take it you called off the ritual?
After my brother pleaded with me to stop.\nOur ideas on what constitutes happiness\nare...different from what I assumed.
We have. I swore to atone for my past\nmistakes by living rather than dying.
Then I'm willing to forget the whole\n＂trapping me in a magic binding spell＂ bit.
Honestly, I'm just happy that you\nand Shion are getting along again.
I am unworthy of such grace.
BUT! If you insist on doing something\nto right your wrongs, keep helping us.
We've all come to depend on you a great\ndeal, you know. So what do you say?
Of course. On behalf of my tribe,\nI shall serve you as long as I live.
I pray that will be a long time indeed.
In that case, welcome back, Delphi.\nWe're happy to have you.
